FCC, Acciona May Bid for Spanish Airports, Expansion Reports

-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s
-- 
2011-09-03T09:24:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-03/fcc-acciona-may-bid-for-spanish-airports-expansion-reports.html
Fomento de Construcciones y
Contratas SA (FCC)  and  Acciona SA (ANA)  may bid for the management contracts
of Madrid-Barajas and Barcelona-El Prat airports,  Expansion 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  FCC may enter the pre-qualification round in partnership
with  Siemens AG (SIE)  and Singapore-based Changi Airport Group, the
newspaper said. Acciona is considering various partners
including Fraport AG, according to Expansion.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Emma Ross-Thomas in Madrid at 
 erossthomas@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  